# Workflow Standards Documentation Maintenance Rule

> **NOTE:** This rule is specific to the **Workflow Rules / Coding Standards** repository. When this repository is integrated into other projects, this rule should be adapted or removed as it references project-specific documentation files (AGENTS.md, INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md, QUICK_INTEGRATION.md, etc.).

## When to Update Documentation

The AI agent MUST review and update documentation whenever:

- **Feature Changes:** New features, modules, or capabilities are added
- **Architecture Changes:** System architecture, patterns, or design decisions change
- **Standards Updates:** Coding standards, conventions, or best practices are modified
- **Process Changes:** Development workflows, commands, or checklists are updated
- **Module Changes:** Modules are added, removed, or significantly modified

## Required Documentation Files to Update

### Root-Level Documentation

1. **`AGENTS.md`** - Project context and memory
   - Update when: Architecture changes, new patterns, major milestones

2. **`CHANGELOG.md`** - Change history
   - Update when: ANY feature, change, or significant update
   - Include timestamp and categorization

3. **`README.md`** - Project overview
   - Update when: Project structure, modules, or quick start instructions change

4. **`STANDARDS_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md`** - Integration instructions
   - Update when: Integration process changes

5. **`QUICK_INTEGRATION.md`** - Quick reference
   - Update when: Integration file lists or quick steps change

### Module-Level Documentation

6. **Module README.md files** (`modules/{module-name}/README.md`)
   - Update when: Module features, API, or usage changes

## Documentation Update Checklist

When making a change, use this checklist:

- [ ] **CHANGELOG.md** - Always updated with timestamp and description
- [ ] **AGENTS.md** - Updated if architecture, patterns, or workflow changed
- [ ] **README.md** - Updated if structure or modules changed
- [ ] **Cross-references** - All links and references verified
- [ ] **Timestamps** - "Last Updated" metadata updated

## Project-Specific Note

**This rule is designed for the Workflow Rules / Coding Standards repository.**

When integrating this repository into other projects:
- **Adapt this rule** to match the target project's documentation structure
- **Remove references** to files that don't exist in the target project
- **Add references** to project-specific documentation files
- **Keep the core principle:** Update documentation when features or architecture change

